2:01 PM; Case called for Plea/sentencing hearing.  Defendant Jerry J Polk in court.  Attorney Conner Helvig in court for Jerry J Polk.  Prosecuting attorney Andrea M Will in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Atty. Helvig advises he has a complete plea questionnaire and is prepared to proceed today.  State advises it is working to file the Amended Information.  Court recites the offer as listed in the plea questionnaire.  State and Defense confirm the offer. Court confirms with counsel they are prepared to proceed with the plea before the Amended Information is filed. Court conducts plea colloquy with the defendant. Defendant enters a guilty plea to Counts 1 & 2 of the Amended Information, Court finds defendant guilty. Atty. Helvig acknowledges receipt of the Amended Information and waives reading.

Sentencing arguments made by the State.
Sentencing arguments made by Atty. Helvig.

COUNT 1:
The Court Orders the Following:

Withheld sentence (Court will award 1 Day Credit IF revoked and sentenced)

Term of Probation: 1 Year & 6 Months

Conditions of Probation:
-	Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
-	Follow any conditions deemed appropriate by Agent;
-	No contact with the Victim listed in the Criminal Complaint unless approved by the Agent and through the Victim's Mother.
-	No violent contact with any minor child;
-	Participate in any additional Parenting Classes to be determined by Agent.  

Condition Time: 30 Days STAYED to be used at the Agents discretion (Huber privileges at the Agent's discretion)

COSTS:  $243.00;

DNA Surcharge: $200.00;

DNA Sample ordered and to be provided immediately if in custody or within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department. 

Total costs/fine/forfeiture:  to be paid as a condition of probation. Failure to pay;  will result in a civil judgment.


